    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1923-12-18T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1923-12-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="281"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d281">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">814.51.An 4/10</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Guatemala</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hewes</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1923-12-18">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 18, 1923</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 664</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The Department has received your despatch No. 452
                    of November 20, 1923, with which you transmit a copy of a letter from Mr. Lionel
                    Stahl discussing the effect of your communication to the Guatemalan Government
                    of the Department’s views regarding the loan contract proposed by Mr. Stahl and
                    his associates.</p>
                <p>The Department approves of your action in declining to discuss the loan
                    proposition further with the Government of Guatemala. The statement of the
                    Department’s opinion as contained in its telegram of November 8, 4 p.m., was
                    definite and final so far as the loan contract at present under discussion is
                    concerned, and it is not felt that this statement requires any amplification or
                    explanation at the present time.</p>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                <closer>For the Secretary of State:<lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Leland Harrison</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
